      • addToMap

        public static <K,​V> Map<K,​V> addToMap​(Map<K,​V> map,
                                                  K key1,
                                                  V value1)
        Adds an item to a map, and returns it. Useful for initialization: doWorkWithMapExample(addToMap( new HashMap<Integer,String>(), 0, "none"));

        Unlike the new HashMap<>() {{ put(x,y); }} pattern, this does not create a new class (which can create problems with de-serialization)

        Type Parameters:
        K - Key type
        V - Value type
        Parameters:
        map - Map to use.
        key1 - First key.
        value1 - Value of first key.
        Returns:
        Returns the map.
        See Also:
        addToMap(Map, Object, Object, Object, Object), addToMap(Map, Object, Object, Object, Object, Object, Object)

      • unmodifiableMap

        public static <K,​V> Map<K,​V> unmodifiableMap​(K key1,
                                                         V value1)
        Creates an unmodifiable map with two items. The returned map is backed by a LinkedHashMap, so it preserves order. Useful for initialization: doWorkWithMapExample(unmodifiableMap(0, "none"));

        Unlike the new HashMap<>() {{ put(x,y); }} pattern, this does not create a new class (which can create problems with de-serialization)

        Type Parameters:
        K - Key type
        V - Value type
        Parameters:
        key1 - First key.
        value1 - Value of first key.
        Returns:
        Returns the map.
        See Also:
        unmodifiableMap(Object, Object, Object, Object), unmodifiableMap(Object, Object, Object, Object, Object, Object)
